	<p pid="a.1.8/1">The shootings of Dadly Lupesya and Nashaz Sakala took place in 2001 during rioting over the re-allocation of funding for road building and that of Epiphania Bonjesi in May 2004 during rioting at the time of elections in May 2004. Following the election, the Minister of Home Affairs confirmed to DfID that it was the government of Malawi's intention to inquire into the shootings in May 2004. He has since advised that investigations are on-going. The Malawi Government have no plans to reopen enquiries into the earlier shootings at present.</p>
</reply>
